                <div class="bg-slate-800 rounded-lg p-6 font-mono text-sm text-green-400 overflow-x-auto shadow-inner border border-slate-700">
                    <p class="mb-4 text-slate-400">// Context: You are a Senior Solution Architect researching a customer.</p>
                    <p class="mb-2"><strong>ACT 1:</strong> Analyze the attached documents [Upload PDFs/Data].</p>
                    <p class="mb-2"><strong>ACT 2:</strong> Structure your response into three tables: People, Process, Technology.</p>
                    <p class="mb-2"><strong>CONSTRAINT 1:</strong> In each table, strictly separate "Verified Facts" (with source citation) from "Inferred Assumptions."</p>
                    <p class="mb-2"><strong>CONSTRAINT 2:</strong> Create a separate list called "The Unknowns" - specific data points missing from the source material that are critical for decision making.</p>
                    <p class="mb-2"><strong>ACT 3:</strong> Generate a Mind Map structure (text-based hierarchy) showing the relationship between [Specific Person] and [Specific Technology].</p>
                    <p class="mb-0"><strong>RECURSION:</strong> After generating, review your own output. Identify 3 areas where the data is weak, and suggest specific questions I should ask the customer to fill these gaps.</p>
                </div>
